---
description: Specific coding standards and conventions for Symfony package development, covering naming conventions.
globs: */src/**/*.*
alwaysApply: false
---
- File names: Use PascalCase (e.g., MyClassFile.php)
- Class and Enum names: Use PascalCase (e.g., MyClass)
- Method names: Use camelCase (e.g., myMethod)
- Variable and Properties names: Use camelCase (e.g., myVariable)
- Constants and Enum Cases names: Use SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., MY_CONSTANT)